07/06/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Three members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in clashes with Turkish security forces in the southeast on Sunday (June 6th), an army source announced.
The first clash involved soldiers who went after a group of rebels that had detonated an explosive device on a road in the Sirnak province.
There was a second clash later in the day, when a group of PKK rebels attacked a police checkpoint in the province.
(Reuters, AFP, Press TV - 06/06/10)
